<br>
Something that not often get parsed is the proc dmg from the pet, basicly I think pets proces add close to 50% extra dmg, it is often you will see a quad hit with a proc in each swing, that is probaly around 550 pt extra dmg that round.<br>
It is hard to know exactly how much dmg the proc do, but you VERY often see the finishing hit a pet make is a 143 hit (max proc dmg). <br>
I been attacked by a charmed epic pet, and it aint fun, I had Fire,Cold and magic resist over 120 and still he stunned me for 3 sec, proced 6 times (all for full) before I could zone (I dropped around 1k hp in the 10sec it took for me to zone).<br>
<br>
Then epicpet then it getting lucky rolls do nasty dmg.<br>
<br>
Of course against normal mobs it can't match a good equiped melee character, and just as add dmg in a group it might look pale. <br>
But solo it kill a grimling skullcracker in Acrylia alot faster than a L60 warrior (warriors mob was still around 40% then pet was finish), of course the 50pt dmg shiled over warriors 33pt helps, the crazy high AC on Grimlings makes pets proces really effective too.<br>
<br>
You just can't compare it to any other pet, I think I heard one epic took on 3 spectrepets at once and still came out on top (ofcourse the dmgshield did most dmg). Even if maybe the normal melee dmg is much higher, just always be able to have a highhp pet with a very good dmg shield mages it worth it.<br>
